title: Homogeneous coordinates
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$V$$ be a an $$F$$-[[vector space|Vektorraum]] and $$(v_1,\dots,v_{n+1})$$ be a [[basis|Basis]]. If

$$
v=\sum_{j=1}^{n+1} x_j v_j,
$$

then for a point $$[v]\in P(V),\ (x_1,\dots,x_{n+1})$$ are called //homogeneous coordinates// of $$[v].$$ These are unique only up to a non-zero factor.
